title: Comment on Stingray had a message for Kentucky on Finebaum by DWade
text:
— Drew Franklin (@DrewFranklinKSR) October 23, 2015 
We’ll never have too much Stingray. After warning Kentucky a couple times earlier in the week, Mississippi State’s sexiest fan was on the Paul Finebaum show for one last message for the Cats. Article written by Drew Franklin I can recite every line from Forrest Gump, blindfolded. Follow me on Twitter: @DrewFranklinKSR 12 responses to “Stingray had a message for Kentucky on Finebaum” ukfan515 October 23, 2015 at 7:13   
Only thing he should be warning UK fans about is heart disease chimichanga October 23, 2015 at 7:17   
Hmm, I wonder if he’s from the South originally? Yummy October 23, 2015 at 7:27   
The things I would do to Stingray… October 23, 2015 at 7:39   
He needs worry more about a Big Mac heart attack! Nuclearcontamination October 23, 2015 at 7:45   
Why you are enamored by this moron is beyond my ability to comprehend. RockyMountainWildcat October 23, 2015 at 7:58   
Why are you giving this clown any attention? Yeah, he’s fat and an attention whore, hilarious… Buie October 23, 2015 at 8:02   
I liked him when he was Frisch’s Big Boy mascot, but now he’s just plain annoying. harry October 23, 2015 at 8:13   
I hate cow bells. Peyton October 23, 2015 at 8:29   
Look, Violet Beauregarde is all grown up. Guess they couldn’t squeeze the juice out of her. UKFAN HAS OUR BACK October 23, 2015 at 8:33   
At least the one UK fan got the bird in there for us at the end! barb getty October 23, 2015 at 9:12
